Package listItLogic

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AddLogic
    This class adds a task to the data file, by breaking down the string command and separates the different variables, in order to create the task object to be added.
    ChangeDirectoryLogic
    This class contains methods which changes the directory of the entire ListIt, by allowing the directory (which includes the data file and the completed data file.
    CommandParser
    This class contains methods which parses the user commands by checking if the command has white space (more than 1 word), or has no white space (1 word only).
    CompleteLogic
    This class contains methods to move tasks from the usual data file, into the completed data file, when the user enters "complete".
    DeleteLogic
    This class contains methods which deletes a particular task from the task list.
    DisplayLogic
    This class contains methods which displays the output(created tasks) as a task list to the user.
    EditLogic
    This class contains methods to edit the selected task.
    ExecuteCommand
    This class contains methods to perform the selection logic action to take, after the command is parsed (by CommandParser).
    HelpLogic
    this class contains the method to activate our help function, which causes another pop up window (that contains all our possible commands) to appear.
    LoggingLogic  
    SearchLogic
    This class contains methods to search for the user input keyword, to find that keyword in our task list.
    TaskCheckLogic
    This class contains all the methods that check if the command date input entered by the user is of a valid date input, and also compares the task date to the actual calendar date.
    UndoAndRedoLogic
    This class contains methods for our redo and undo logic; 2 temporary stacks are created and the task lists are stored into these stacks.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    InvalidCommandException
    This class is used to extend the exceptions that occurs in ListIt by creating an InvalidCommandException, therefore, providing a code of higher quality.
